One subtle spacing issue I find quite annoying that I run into a lot is leading tabs before variable names after type definition.<p>IE:<p><pre><code>  int        anInt    = 7;
  String     aString  = "My string value";
  ClassName  aClass   = new ClassName();
</code></pre>
In this example it's not the bad because the typedefs are few, trivial and short and there is actually a leader between the words (.). However, in real code where you have longer class names used in tandem with standard types like int or String as well has some times a dozen definitions--suddenly you wish you had a ruler you can put on the screen.<p><pre><code>  int                      anInt            = 7;
  Service_Ups              Svc              = new Service_Ups();
  ClassNamesCanGetLong     variableNamesToo = new ClassNamesCanGetLong();</code></pre>
